The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | 3 get RI in riots case
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      3 get RI in riots case
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, April 30: Three persons were today convicted by a fast-track court and sentenced to five years rigorous imprisonment along with Rs 2,000 fine for involvement in the 2008 communal riots in Kandhamal.        
	One Ishwar Dandia was sentenced to five years RI and imposed a penalty of Rs 2,000 on charges of unlawful assembly with weapons and torching houses belonging to minority community in Raikela village during the riots.         
	Kamadeb Pradhan and Balaji Pradhan were also sentenced the same for torching some houses in Midabali village.                                                                                                                                                           
